{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"ir","display_name":"R","language":"R"},"language_info":{"name":"R","codemirror_mode":"r","pygments_lexer":"r","mimetype":"text/x-r-source","file_extension":".r","version":"4.0.5"}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"code","source":"# This R environment comes with many helpful analytics packages installed\n# It is defined by the kaggle/rstats Docker image: https://github.com/kaggle/docker-rstats\n# For example, here's a helpful package to load\n\nlibrary(tidyverse) # metapackage of all tidyverse packages\n\n# Input data files are available in the read-only \"../input/\" directory\n# For example, running this (by clicking run or pressing Shift+Enter) will list all files under the input directory\n\nlist.files(path = \"../input\")\n\n# You can write up to 20GB to the current directory (/kaggle/working/) that gets preserved as output when you create a version using \"Save & Run All\" \n# You can also write temporary files to /kaggle/temp/, but they won't be saved outside of the current session","metadata":{"_uuid":"051d70d956493feee0c6d64651c6a088724dca2a","_execution_state":"idle","execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T13:35:44.887789Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T13:35:44.889317Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T13:35:44.908991Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# 2 Hands On: Data Quality and Pre-Processing","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 1. Assessing Data Quality","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Load the following packages: dplyr, na.tools, tidyimpute (version from github\ndecisionpatterns/tidyimpute”)**\n\n**Load the carInsurance data set about the insurance risk rating of cars based on several characteristics of\neach car1**\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"cardf <- read.csv(\"/kaggle/input/ucmachinelearning/imports-85.data\")\nhead(cardf)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T14:21:37.089824Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T14:21:37.091973Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T14:21:37.164659Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"colnames(cardf) <- c(\"symboling\", \"normalized-losses\", \"make\", \"fuel-type\", \"aspiration\", \"nDoors\", \"body-style\", \"drive-wheels\", \"engine-location\", \"wheel-base\", \"length\", \"width\", \"height\", \"curb-weight\", \"engine-type\", \"num-of-cylinders\", \"engine-size\", \"fuel-system\", \"bore\", \"stroke\", \"compression-ratio\", \"horsepower\", \"peak-rpm\", \"city-mpg\", \"highway-mpg\", \"price\")\n\nhead(cardf)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T14:29:30.283773Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T14:29:30.285538Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T14:29:30.339226Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(a) Check if there are any missing values.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"vall_null <- sum(is.na(cardf) | cardf == \"?\")\n\nprint(paste(\"Casos con valores nulos: \", vall_null))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T14:32:04.545033Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T14:32:04.546379Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T14:32:04.562674Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(b) Count the number of cases that have, at least, one missing value.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"vall_null2 <- colSums(is.na(cardf) | cardf == \"?\")\n\nvall_null2[vall_null2 >= 0]","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T14:32:45.117903Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T14:32:45.119234Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T14:32:45.138125Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(c) Create a new data set by removing all the cases that have missing values**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"cardf[cardf == \"?\"] <- NA\ncardf_clean <- cardf[complete.cases(cardf), ]\n\nhead(cardf_clean)\nval_null <- sum(is.na(cardf_clean))\nprint(paste(\"Valores nulos: \", val_null))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T14:35:18.364344Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T14:35:18.365689Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T14:35:18.413954Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(d) Create a new data set by imputing all the missing values with 0.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"cardf_miss <- replace(cardf, is.na(cardf), 0)\n\nhead(cardf_miss)\nval_null2 <- sum(is.na(cardf_miss))\nprint(paste(\"Valores nulos: \", val_null2))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T14:35:34.196799Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T14:35:34.198195Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T14:35:34.241057Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(e) Create a new data set by imputing the mean in all the columns which have double type values**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"library(zoo)\n\nnew_cardf <- cardf\nnuw_col <- sapply(new_cardf, is.numeric)\nnew_cardf[, nuw_col] <- na.aggregate(new_cardf[, nuw_col], FUN = mean)\n\nhead(new_cardf)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T14:41:39.676200Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T14:41:39.677520Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T14:41:39.720518Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(f) Create a new data set by imputing the mode in all the columns which have integer type values**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"#Buscar el mode con una funcion\nmode <- function(x) {\n  unico <- unique(x)\n  unico[which.max(tabulate(match(x, unico)))]\n}\n#Columnas con valores tipo integer\ncol_int <- sapply(cardf, is.integer)\n\ncardf_imp <- cardf\n\nfor (columna in names(cardf_imp)[col_int]) {\n  val_null3 <- is.na(cardf_imp[[columna]])\n  modo <- mode(cardf_imp[[columna]])\n  cardf_imp[[columna]][val_null3] <- modo\n}\n\nhead(cardf_imp)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T14:41:02.562186Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T14:41:02.563914Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T14:41:02.621628Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(g) Create a new data set by imputing the most frequent value to the column ”nDoors”**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"mode <- function(x) {\n  unico <- unique(x)\n  unico[which.max(tabulate(match(x, unico)))]\n}\n\nnDoors_mode <- mode(cardf$nDoors)\n\ncardf_imp2 <- cardf\ncardf_imp2$nDoors[is.na(cardf_imp2$nDoors)] <- nDoors_mode\n\nhead(cardf_imp2)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T14:44:29.183505Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T14:44:29.184854Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T14:44:29.224078Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(h) Combine the three last imputations to obtain a final dataset. Are there any duplicated cases?**\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"","metadata":{},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# 2. Data Pre-Processing","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 2. Load the package dlookr. Use the same car insurance data set above and apply the following transformations to the price attribute. Be critical regarding the obtained results.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(a) Apply range-based normalization and z-score normalization.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"cardf$price <- as.numeric(cardf$price)\nrange_normalized <- transform(cardf, range_normalized = (price - min(price, na.rm = TRUE)) / (max(price, na.rm = TRUE) - min(price, na.rm = TRUE)))\n\nzscore_normalized <- transform(cardf, zscore_normalized = scale(price))\n\nhead(range_normalized)\nhead(zscore_normalized)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T14:56:08.813860Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T14:56:08.815291Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T14:56:08.879392Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(b) Discretize it into 4 equal-frequency ranges an into 4 equal-width ranges.**\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"equal_freq_ranges <- cut(cardf$price, breaks = 4, labels = FALSE, include.lowest = TRUE)\n\nequal_width_ranges <- cut(cardf$price, breaks = 4, labels = FALSE, include.lowest = TRUE, dig.lab = 4)\n\nhead(equal_freq_ranges)\nhead(equal_width_ranges)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T14:59:18.302292Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T14:59:18.303664Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T14:59:18.324173Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 3. With the seed 111019 obtain the following samples on the car insurance data set.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"set.seed(111019)\n\nsample1 <- cardf[sample(nrow(cardf), min(100, nrow(cardf)), replace = FALSE), ]\n\nsample2 <- cardf[sample(nrow(cardf), min(200, nrow(cardf)), replace = FALSE), ]\n\nsample3 <- cardf[sample(nrow(cardf), min(300, nrow(cardf)), replace = FALSE), ]\n\nhead(sample1)\nhead(sample2)\nhead(sample3)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T15:03:39.238969Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T15:03:39.241806Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T15:03:39.388595Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(a) A random sample of 60% of the cases, with replacement**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"set.seed(111019)\n\nsample_size <- round(0.6 * nrow(cardf))\n\nsample_with_replacement <- cardf[sample(nrow(cardf), sample_size, replace = TRUE), ]\nhead(sample_with_replacement)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T15:06:51.761409Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T15:06:51.766437Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T15:06:51.822085Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(b) A stratified sample of 60% of the cases of cars, according to the fuelType attribute**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"set.seed(111019)\n\nstratified_sample <- cardf[ave(seq(nrow(cardf)), cardf$\"fuel-type\", FUN = function(x) sample(x, size = round(0.6 * length(x)))), ]\n\nhead(stratified_sample)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T15:12:38.651561Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T15:12:38.652847Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T15:12:38.701060Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(c) Use the table() function to inspect the distribution of values in each of the two samples above.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"table_random <- table(sample_with_replacement$\"fuel-type\")\nprint(table_random)\n\ntable_stratified <- table(stratified_sample$\"fuel-type\")\nprint(table_stratified)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T15:14:19.216899Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T15:14:19.218258Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T15:14:19.235747Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 4. Load the package corrplot and select the numeric attributes of the car insurance data set.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"num_attri <- cardf[sapply(cardf, is.numeric)]\n\nhead(num_attri)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T15:19:16.324343Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T15:19:16.325779Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T15:19:16.354064Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(a) Using the function cor(), obtain the pearson correlation coefficient between each pair of variables.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"correl_matrix <- cor(num_attri, use = \"pairwise.complete.obs\")\n\nprint(correl_matrix)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T15:20:05.105872Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T15:20:05.107101Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T15:20:05.128853Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(b) Apply the function cor.mtest() to the previous result to calculate the p-values and confidence intervals of the correlation coefficient for each pair of variables.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"correl_matrix <- cor(correl_matrix, use = \"pairwise.complete.obs\")\n\ncorrelation_tests <- cor.mtest(correl_matrix, conf.level = 0.95)\n\nprint(correlation_tests)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T15:26:10.368170Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T15:26:10.370199Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T15:26:10.404719Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(c) Plot the all correlation information using the function corrplot. Explore some of its parameters**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"correlation_matrix <- cor(num_attri, use = \"pairwise.complete.obs\")\n\ncorrplot(correlation_matrix, method = \"circle\", type = \"upper\", tl.cex = 0.8, tl.col = \"black\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T15:26:42.773508Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T15:26:42.778565Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T15:26:43.075028Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 5. Load the data set USJudgeRatings, from the datasets package, containing lawyers’ ratings of state judges in the US Superior Court regarding a set of attributes.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"judgedf <- read.csv(\"/kaggle/input/data2dd/dataset-29460 (1).csv\")\n\nhead(judgedf)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T15:41:13.185144Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T15:41:13.186422Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T15:41:13.223148Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(a) Apply the function prcomp() to obtain the principal components. Inspect how each variable is obtained by the linear combination of each component.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"library(dplyr)\nnumeric_judgedf <- select_if(judgedf, is.numeric)\nnumeric_judgedf <- na.omit(numeric_judgedf)\npca <- prcomp(numeric_judgedf)\nvariable_loadings <- pca$rotation\nprint(variable_loadings)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T15:46:25.537162Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T15:46:25.539819Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T15:46:25.621535Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**(b) Load the package ggbiplot and plot the two first components with the function ggbiplot(). You can label each point with the lawyer’s name by setting the labels parameter.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"numeric_judgedf <- judgedf[, sapply(judgedf, is.numeric)]\n\npca <- prcomp(numeric_judgedf[, -1])\n\nscores <- as.data.frame(pca$x[, 1:2])\n\nscores$lawyer <- judgedf$CONT\n\nlibrary(ggplot2)\n\nggplot(scores, aes(PC1, PC2, color = lawyer)) +\n  geom_point() +\n  labs(title = \"Principal Component Analysis\") +\n  theme_minimal()","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-06-12T15:51:43.798308Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-06-12T15:51:43.802855Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-06-12T15:51:45.521143Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]}]}